{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02655/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02655"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:26:55"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman smiles."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02655","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02655"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1/fd8813ed-510a-4639-b362-721a38e1bfb3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:51:29.479Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Amy Greenhough, reading <em>Phantom Thread</em> through the lens of fairy tales and the politics of labor, notes, “Alma’s body is...essential to her role, because were she to become pregnant or to gain or lose weight, it is likely that she would be unable to maintain her job. The specificity of Alma’s body is key too—the way she walks and moves is something that Reynolds observes with interest, his intense gaze locking on to her from the beginning. ...he simultaneously reveals that he sees her body as his to mold with his dresses. There is an awkward separation of mind and body here with the body as a kind of tabula rasa that the designer can shape as he pleases, which paradoxically suggests disembodiment within the labor context” (Greenhough, “Spinning Bodies into Gold,” 194).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02655/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:861.8034993270525,149.1520861372813,817.8734858681024,764.8990578734858"}}}]}]}]}